HEADWORD: expanded
<hw>expanded</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>increased in extent or size or
bulk or scope. Opposite of <ant>contracted</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms:
<stype>blown-up, enlarged</stype>; <stype>dilated</stype>;
<stype>distended, swollen</stype>; <stype>inflated</stype>]⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Printnig)</fld> <def>wider than usual for a
particular height; -- of printers' type. Contrasted with
<ant>condensed</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> extended.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

